# Active project rules block

First substantive reply per chat / mode change → emit **once**, before plan / code:

```markdown
### Active project rules
- `<subfolder>/<rule>.mdc`
- ...
```

- Bullet every active `.mdc` (skip `*.disabled`); add @-mentioned and matching glob rules.
- Re-emit on mode/topic change or when asked which rules apply. Skip on tool-only follow-ups.
- ≤20-word ack may precede the heading—nothing else above.
